Seven former Tongaat Hulett executives charged with R3,5-billion fraud have been officially served with an indictment.  The accused include former CEO Peter Staude (58), CFO Murray Hector Munro (55), director Michael Edward Deighton (57), director Rory Edward Wilkinson (50), legal executive Kamasagrie Singh (56), finance executive Samantha Shukla (50) and former auditor at Deloitte and Touche, Gavin Dykes Kruger (56). The seven former executives appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crimes Court on Monday morning.  They all face charges of fraud amounting to about R3,5Â billion, as well as charges of Contravention of the Financial Markets Act, Companies Act, and Prevention of Organised Crime Act (Poca). ALSO READ | No racketeering charge yet for ex-Tongaat Hulett executives Natasha Ramkisson-Kara, National Prosecuting Authority KZN spokesperson said the state served the accused, by way of their legal representatives, with the indictment.  Ramkisson-Kara said the indictment includes racketeering charges authorised by the National Director of Public Prosecutions. The accused are facing 26 counts of fraud. According to the indictment, it is alleged that a common purpose existed between the accused to commit the crimes of fraud. The case was adjourned to September 15, in the Durban high court.